260
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:46,120
Your best friend needs your help, and you're tired?

261
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:48,520
Tired who, tired how? I'm tired because I spent all day

262
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:50,820
wondering whether someone was going to shout "surprise" at me,

263
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:52,800
and no-one fucking did.

264
00:17:55,570 --> 00:17:57,100
That's why.

265
00:17:58,390 --> 00:18:00,180
And it's made me tired.

266
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:04,800
Shout "surprise"... What?! No, come on, you're not even making sense.

267
00:18:05,380 --> 00:18:07,080
You're right.

268
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:10,470
I'm just going back to my computer game, OK?

269
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:13,320
It goes all funny if you leave it on pause for too long.

270
00:18:17,190 --> 00:18:18,560
But I don't...

271
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:22,330
get it.

272
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:28,470
Contact neutralised. Fine!

273
00:18:55,710 --> 00:18:56,940
What?

274
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:01,420
Are you going to try and hurt me again?

275
00:19:02,730 --> 00:19:05,710
Because if you are, just get on with it, I've had a really shit day.

276
00:19:18,230 --> 00:19:22,460
I don't have favourites. Yeah, but you're worried about him.

277
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:24,980
What did he do to you?

278
00:19:24,980 --> 00:19:27,250
He zipped my mouth shut.

279
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:29,580
And he's sleeping with Jay?

280
00:19:29,580 --> 00:19:32,570
Yes. Behind my back.

281
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:34,880
I don't know what's going on with this town...

282
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:37,640
and I don't know what's going on with my son, either.

283
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:42,560
It'd just be nice if you could... worry about me too.

284
00:19:43,130 --> 00:19:46,440
I do... worry about you.

285
00:19:50,170 --> 00:19:51,990
Paul. I'm going to bed, Mum.

286
00:19:51,990 --> 00:19:54,480
You been out celebrating with Mac?

287
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:57,720
Celebrating... what? Look, I'm tired.

288
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,410
Don't you think we should talk?

289
00:20:00,410 --> 00:20:03,510
I'm really... busy at the moment, Mum, OK?

290
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:06,300
Yeah! I know.

291
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,380
Celebrating what?

292
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,830
Oh, shit!

293
00:20:45,930 --> 00:20:50,240
HAPPY BIRTH-YESTER-DAY 17+1

294
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:55,350
It took three cans of shaving foam.

295
00:20:55,620 --> 00:20:58,210
The newsagent thought I was going for a whole body shave.

296
00:20:58,210 --> 00:21:02,190
He advised me against it. Apparently, pubic stubble rash is a killer.

297
00:21:02,190 --> 00:21:05,940
Good to know. What's a surprise if you're sort of expecting it?

298
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:10,230
The truly surprising birthday is one that takes place a day late.

299
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:11,910
So true.

300
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:15,960
I'm still learning how to...

301
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:20,730
balance who I am with what I... I know.

302
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:26,610
And you're probably still trying to balance who I am with what I...

303
00:21:26,610 --> 00:21:28,020
I am.

304
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:30,960
And I've always been a bit self-centred. You have.

305
00:21:33,380 --> 00:21:35,220
And I'm sorry.

306
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:38,910
Did I mention that I'm sorry?

307
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:46,640
How long were you waiting out here before I opened the curtains?

308
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,210
It was a while.

309
00:21:57,980 --> 00:22:00,500
After three? Always.

310
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:03,020
One, two...

311
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:11,650
It's not the magic number. Far more likely to be seven.

312
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:14,110
Way more pagan connotations.

313
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:17,040
Also, a much more satisfying number to say.

314
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,790
Seven. Seven.

315
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:21,120
Se-ven.

316
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:30,150
Zap! You see that? Did ya?

317
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:32,100
Yeah. Did you see that?

318
00:22:32,570 --> 00:22:34,840
Mama say knock you out.

319
00:22:42,370 --> 00:22:43,320
Paul? 

320
00:22:44,870 --> 00:22:45,930
Paul?

321
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:49,380
Paul? Paul? Paul!

322
00:22:49,380 --> 00:22:51,030
Paul! Paul!

323
00:23:10,590 --> 00:23:11,830
So...

324
00:23:14,630 --> 00:23:18,070
This is... inevitable.

325
00:23:26,430 --> 00:23:27,780
What was that?

326
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,240
I need to go to see Neil.

327
00:23:33,910 --> 00:23:35,100
Was that a fit?

328
00:23:35,710 --> 00:23:37,920
I had a cousin who was an epileptic. Well, he thought he was...

329
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,790
turned out he was just overtired, so...

330
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:41,100
I'm sorry.

331
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:44,150
Happy birth-yester-day.

332
00:23:44,150 --> 00:23:46,350
I need... I need to go, alone.

333
00:23:46,350 --> 00:23:49,290
Of course you do. I'll be waiting.

334
00:24:08,830 --> 00:24:09,810
Hold still.

335
00:24:09,810 --> 00:24:12,340
Right, who are you? And what are you doing here?

336
00:24:12,340 --> 00:24:14,950
What? No, who are you? Let's try again, eh?

337
00:24:14,950 --> 00:24:19,760
Who are you, and what are you doing? I'm... here to see Neil.

338
00:24:20,980 --> 00:24:22,600
You're Paul, aren't you?

339
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:29,150
This is him? We heard all about you.

340
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:34,580
Thank you... for coming so quickly. Um...

341
00:24:34,860 --> 00:24:38,350
I... You're here because... You look like shit, Neil.

342
00:24:38,350 --> 00:24:40,540
I'll get to that. Start with that.

343
00:24:40,540 --> 00:24:41,930
Who attacked you? Can I just...?

344
00:24:41,930 --> 00:24:45,840
Neil, the only way to sort out our fears is to tell us what's going on.

345
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:49,460
OK. Just to make clear - I didn't want you here,

346
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:52,050
so fuck you if you think I'm not doing this my way!

347
00:24:52,050 --> 00:24:56,600
There's a problem. The Fades can touch.

348
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,710
And they're attacking us.

349
00:24:58,710 --> 00:25:01,860
They seem to be able to do this because they're eating human flesh,

350
00:25:01,860 --> 00:25:04,190
and we have no idea how to stop them. Well,

351
00:25:04,190 --> 00:25:07,860
that didn't make my fears go away. Anyone else's fears go away?

352
00:25:07,860 --> 00:25:10,850
Sorry, but there you are. So we're in danger?

353
00:25:10,850 --> 00:25:12,660
But we're not without hope. Why?

354
00:25:12,660 --> 00:25:15,340
Because we've got a little kid who can save the world, eh?

355
00:25:15,340 --> 00:25:17,430
A boy who I wouldn't even trust with a spud gun!

356
00:25:17,430 --> 00:25:20,310
He has powers we don't even understand yet.

357
00:25:20,780 --> 00:25:23,070
Eric thinks he's special.

358
00:25:23,580 --> 00:25:26,320
Neil thinks he's special. Can I...?

359
00:25:26,690 --> 00:25:29,010
As we're talking about me, shall I...?

360
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:30,780
Neil!

361
00:25:33,770 --> 00:25:37,870
Oh, Jesus, Neil. You've been walking around with that?

362
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:40,550
For fuck's sake, how many dead Angelics do we need?

363
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:44,960
Let me look at him.

364
00:25:47,660 --> 00:25:49,360
I can help him. Let me look at him.

365
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:55,180
You can help, can you?

366
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:59,500
Trust me. Trust you?

367
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:01,980
I told you to be careful, didn't I?

368
00:26:01,980 --> 00:26:04,370
Then you let Alice and Phil jump you.

369
00:26:04,370 --> 00:26:07,290
That's nothing. The Fade girl follows me everywhere.

370
00:26:07,290 --> 00:26:11,080
She could probably jump me at any time.
Natalie? You stay away from her.

371
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:13,010
Look at me. You stay away from her!

372
00:26:13,010 --> 00:26:16,050
Paul, you're not ready.
OK.

373
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:23,500
This probably won't hurt. Before you do this...

374
00:26:23,910 --> 00:26:25,620
Do you know what you're doing?

375
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:30,440
Not even close. Feels right.

376
00:26:56,260 --> 00:26:57,720
Just let it happen.

377
00:27:11,490 --> 00:27:13,020
Tickle, don't they?

378
00:27:20,450 --> 00:27:22,890
How do I look? Your eye...

379
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:25,770
He's done things I never could.

380
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:40,160
There was a reason I came to see you today.

381
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:44,470
Well, I hope it's because I called you, several times.

382
00:27:45,530 --> 00:27:47,200
I had another vision.

383
00:27:48,390 --> 00:27:50,990
Same as before, except there was a man in it.

384
00:27:51,730 --> 00:27:54,290
He smiled at me, and then it cut out.

385
00:27:56,580 --> 00:27:57,630
Is...? 

386
00:28:01,420 --> 00:28:03,860
Am I seeing the end of the world, Neil?

387
00:28:04,690 --> 00:28:08,160
Who was the man? Did you recognise him?

388
00:28:09,490 --> 00:28:10,670
No...

389
00:28:14,130 --> 00:28:16,430
I want you to move in here, with us.

390
00:28:16,430 --> 00:28:19,130
Just until this is over. No. I can't.

391
00:28:20,310 --> 00:28:23,630
Can't. I've got people to see.

392
00:28:24,070 --> 00:28:28,840
What you just did in there, to help me, was extraordinary.

393
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:30,020
Extraordinary.

394
00:28:30,020 --> 00:28:32,760
But the fact you can do that, that makes you valuable.

395
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:34,920
OK, fine. Don't move in here.

396
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:37,950
But there is someone out there that scares me.

397
00:28:37,950 --> 00:28:40,170
So you just promise me this. Promise me

398
00:28:40,170 --> 00:28:43,560
you won't ignore the "kill me" signs we've all got on our backs.

399
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:45,940
I need my own life, Neil.

400
00:28:45,940 --> 00:28:48,600
Again, you're not listening to a word I say.

401
00:29:03,250 --> 00:29:07,000
We need to capture one of them.
What, with our ghost rope?

402
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,810
If they can touch you, you can touch them.

403
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:13,690
Hey, we have a code, remember? Which they broke first.

404
00:29:14,190 --> 00:29:17,790
It's time for us to act. Phil is right. We need to spread out,

405
00:29:17,790 --> 00:29:20,090
find smaller, weaker Fades.

406
00:29:20,090 --> 00:29:22,650
We do this now, before they get too strong.

407
00:29:22,650 --> 00:29:27,770
And then what do we do, eh? Once we find this smaller, weaker Fade?

408
00:29:28,660 --> 00:29:30,530
We find out its limits.

409
00:29:46,350 --> 00:29:49,230
Neil. Hello, Mark.

410
00:29:49,780 --> 00:29:52,810
I've been... I've been looking...

411
00:29:52,810 --> 00:29:55,000
How did you know I've been looking for you?

412
00:29:55,230 --> 00:29:56,500
I didn't.

413
00:29:57,070 --> 00:30:01,000
Mark, I'm not here for small talk. I'm here as a translator.

414
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,380
A translator? Are you going to invite me in?

415
00:30:13,310 --> 00:30:16,090
What were you doing with my wife in a mental hospital?

416
00:30:18,690 --> 00:30:23,130
I was rescuing her. I'll go through to the lounge, yeah?

417
00:30:23,130 --> 00:30:25,050
I didn't think you'd ever come.

418
00:30:27,950 --> 00:30:29,790
I almost died this afternoon.

419
00:30:32,410 --> 00:30:34,800
It reminded me I had things to put right.

420
00:30:35,110 --> 00:30:38,920
You're going to put us right, are you? I'm going to try.

421
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,330
Who are you talking to?

422
00:30:41,870 --> 00:30:43,390
Sarah's dead.

423
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:46,450
You don't know that.

424
00:30:47,970 --> 00:30:50,960
I do.
I'm sorry.

425
00:30:52,990 --> 00:30:54,760
She's also a spirit

426
00:30:55,530 --> 00:30:59,220
who has decided that the best use of her time is to follow you around.

427
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:04,040
She's... what?

428
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:07,620
This I'm also sorry about, because I think she's wrong.

429
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:11,760
But it's what she wants,

430
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:14,520
so I want to do the decent thing by her.

431
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:17,390
That's why I'm here as a translator, because...

432
00:31:18,190 --> 00:31:20,210
I can talk to ghosts.

433
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:23,410
